      "parameters": [
        {
          "name": "time",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The timestamp, in seconds, at which to render the scene."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This method can be used only with an "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnrenderer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object created with the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnrenderer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " initializer. Call this method to tell SceneKit to draw the renderer’s scene into the OpenGL context you created the renderer with."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When you call this method, SceneKit updates its hierarchy of presentation nodes based on the specified timestamp, and then draws the scene."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "By default, the playback timing of actions and animations in a scene is based on the system time, not the scene time. Before using this method to control the playback of animations, set the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/quartzcore/caanimation/1523819-usesscenetimebase"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " property of each animation to "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": false,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/yes"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", or specify the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnscenesourceanimationimportpolicyplayusingscenetimebase"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " option when loading a scene file that contains animations."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "note",
          "name": "Note"
        }
      ]
    }
